# Meta Marketing API (Facebook + Instagram Ads)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to get these:
#   1. Create / open a Meta Business Settings account
#      https://business.facebook.com/settings
#   2. Business Settings → Users → System Users → "Add" (Admin role)
#   3. Click the system user → "Generate New Token"
#      - App: pick the app you registered with Marketing API permissions
#      - Permissions: ads_management, ads_read, business_management,
#        read_insights, pages_read_engagement (as needed)
#      - Token expiry: NEVER  ← important for long-lived broker use
#   4. Business Settings → Accounts → Ad Accounts → assign the system user
#      with the role you need (Admin for write, Analyst for read-only)
#   5. Find your Ad Account ID: Ads Manager top-left dropdown shows
#      "act_<numeric>" — copy the number

META_ACCESS_TOKEN=             # the long-lived system-user token
META_AD_ACCOUNT_ID=            # numeric (broker auto-prefixes "act_")

# Optional. Defaults to v21.0 inside the broker if unset.
# META_GRAPH_VERSION=v21.0
